Plug-in name: Nonterm
Plug-in shortname: nonterm
Description:
Warns when definitively non-terminating functions/loops are detected (e.g. reachable functions with unreachable returns).

Most options of the form '-nonterm-option-name' and without any parameter
have an opposite with the name '-nonterm-no-option-name'.

Most options of the form '-option-name' and without any parameter
have an opposite with the name '-no-option-name'.

Options taking a string as argument should preferably be written
-option-name="argument".

***** LIST OF AVAILABLE OPTIONS:

-nonterm            when on (off by default), warns about non-terminating
                    functions/loops (opposite option is -no-nonterm)
-nonterm-dead-code  warns about syntactically unreachable code. Note that
                    this may emit a substantial amount of warnings. (opposite
                    option is -nonterm-no-dead-code)
-nonterm-ignore <f1,..,fn>  ignore functions f1,..,fn and direct calls to
                    them. Functions prefixed with '-' are removed from the
                    ignore list. Calls via function pointers are never
                    ignored. By default, the following functions are ignored:
                    abort, exit (preferably use -nonterm-ignore="f1,..,fn")

*** DEBUG

-nonterm-debug <n>  level of debug for plug-in Nonterm (default to 0)

*** GETTING INFORMATION

-nonterm-help       help of plug-in Nonterm
-nonterm-h          alias for option -nonterm-help

*** OUTPUT MESSAGES

-nonterm-log <K_1:file_1,...>  copy log messages from Nonterm to a file. <K>
                    is a combination of these characters:
                    a: ALL messages (equivalent to 'dfiruw')
                    d: debug       e: user or internal error (same as 'iu')
                    f: feedback    i: internal error
                    r: result      u: user error    w: warning
                    An empty <K> (e.g. ":file.txt") defaults to 'iruw'. One
                    plug-in can output to several files and vice-versa.
                    (preferably use -nonterm-log="K_1:file_1,...")
-nonterm-msg-key <k1[,...,kn]>  enables message display for categories
                    <k1>,...,<kn>. Use -nonterm-msg-key help to get a list of
                    available categories, and * to enable all categories
                    (preferably use -nonterm-msg-key="k1[,...,kn]")
-nonterm-verbose <n>  level of verbosity for plug-in Nonterm (default to 1)
-nonterm-warn-key <k1[=s1][,...,kn[=sn]]>  set warning status for category
                    <k1> to <s1>,...,<kn> to <sn>. Use -nonterm-warn-key help
                    to get a list of available categories, and * to enable
                    all categories. Possible statuses are inactive, feedback,
                    warning, error, abort, feedback-once, warning-once,
                    error-once. Defaults to warning. (preferably use
                    -nonterm-warn-key="k1[=s1][,...,kn[=sn]]")
